        <p>The sources provide numerous examples of how researchers can utilize AI tools in TCM:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Data Mining and Knowledge Discovery:</strong> Apply AI techniques like machine learning, deep learning, and natural language processing to analyze large datasets of TCM literature, clinical records, and research findings.</li>
            <li><strong>Network Pharmacology:</strong> Combine network analysis with pharmacology to study the complex interactions between drugs, targets, and diseases.</li>
            <li><strong>Precision TCM:</strong> Develop personalized TCM treatments by analyzing patient data, symptoms, and genetic information for more targeted therapies.</li>
            <li><strong>Clinical Trial Design and Analysis:</strong> Assist in designing and analyzing clinical trials for TCM interventions by identifying patient cohorts and optimizing protocols.</li>
            <li><strong>Literature Review and Synthesis:</strong> Automate literature searches and synthesize findings from multiple studies, improving efficiency and comprehensiveness.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

